  </table>

  <div class="kbox kbox-red" style="margin-top:14px;">
    <span class="kbox-label">EXAM TRAP: Purification Pitfalls</span>
    <strong>Removing NaHCO₃ from Na₂CO₃ solid:</strong> Heat! NaHCO₃ decomposes: 2NaHCO₃ →(Δ) Na₂CO₃ + CO₂↑ + H₂O. Na₂CO₃ is stable at this temperature. ✓<br><br>
    <strong>Purifying H₂ gas containing CO₂ and NH₃:</strong> First pass through NaOH(aq) to remove CO₂ (CO₂+2NaOH→Na₂CO₃+H₂O). Then dry with CaO (to remove water and NH₃).<br><br>
    <strong>AlCl₃ cannot be obtained by evaporating AlCl₃ solution</strong> — Al³⁺ hydrolyses during evaporation: Al³⁺ + 3H₂O → Al(OH)₃ + 3H⁺, then HCl evaporates, leaving Al(OH)₃. Must evaporate in atmosphere of HCl gas.
  </div>
