<div class="card">
  <h4>Procedure & How It Works</h4>
  <div class="kbox kbox-amber">
    <span class="kbox-label">Standard Procedure (3 steps)</span>
    <strong>1. Clean the wire:</strong> Dip nichrome wire in conc. HCl, hold in roaring Bunsen flame. Repeat until no colour — wire is clean.<br>
    <strong>2. Pick up sample:</strong> Dip clean wire into the metal salt (solid or solution).<br>
    <strong>3. Observe:</strong> Hold wire at edge of Bunsen flame (not the roaring blue part — the cooler yellow-tip area). Observe colour immediately.
  </div>
  <div class="kbox kbox-purple">
    <span class="kbox-label">Why it works</span>
    Heat excites electrons in metal atoms → electrons promoted to higher energy levels → electrons fall back to ground state → release energy as photons of specific wavelengths → characteristic colour. This is emission spectroscopy visible to the naked eye.
  </div>
</div>
